      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/3/78 ¶ Strictly Private ¶  ¶ I need not assure you, dear Mr Ramsay, that I will be happy to support your candidature at the R.S., ¶ Royal Society, London.Ramsay was never nominated for election to ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.03.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-91, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22/3/78</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Strictly Private</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I need not assure you, dear Mr Ramsay, that I will be happy to support your candidature at the R.S.,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Society, London.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ramsay was never nominated for election to the Society<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see Home (2003)).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but this months mail is gone. So perhaps you will advise me to whom to write. I will gladly write to our venerable friend Prof. Owen, who will likely be the next president,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Owen was never President of the Royal Society.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and if Lord<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Lewis's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>adress is given me,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Not identified. There was no<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Fellow<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the Royal Society with this<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>surname<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in 1878.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will readily communicate with him also.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is plenty of time till next mail. Can you confidentially give me some clue to the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">real</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>feelings of Moore towards me? How is it, that he instead of bravely supporting my Directorship so<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">eagerly</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recommends that I should<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">accept</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the change, when I had nothing to accept, but was simply deprived homeless of my whole Department and thus thrown into abject poverty? How is that Mr Francis,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Francis.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>after seeing mere lawns and not even a glass-house (for £8000 a year there) at your Garden, so soon as he came back in 1873 from the Sydney conference, resolved, that there "must be here a change".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>See C. Moore to J. Hooker,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>24 February 1873<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as M73-02-24).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I never shall forget<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">that</hi>
               </seg>! Mr M. has promised me plants from Lord Howes Isl; but none have come for months;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>See C. Moore<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to G. Bentham, 19 February 1876<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as M76-02-19).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he also tells me, that I shall have a set of his N. Guinea plants; perhaps his collector is not yet back.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My own impression is, that at least cautiously &amp;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">indirectly</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he has contributed after all my generosity to him as much to my ruin &amp; deep sadness &amp; distress, as the man in Adelaide.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Richard Schomburgk.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Is jealousy the spring of this like at Kew? Hooker gives [me pur]posely<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Paper damaged.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; studiously<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">no support</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>though (except Owen) all men of science rallied round him against Ayrton.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See MacLeod (1974).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>H. wants merely<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">collectors</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the Colonial establishments &amp; Kew is to monopolize all of British wri[ting]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Word partly illegible. There is no signature, suggesting that at least one page of the letter is missing.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
